rd-looking; innovation respecting heritage; proud Malaysians embracing progress"},{"value":"Pride Point","importance":"Sensitivity","expression":"Usage Notes","marketing_angle":""},{"value":"Independence (Merdeka, 31 August 1957)","importance":"Low","expression":"Major celebration; Tunku Abdul Rahman revered; \"Merdeka\" spirit positive; safe for patriotic messaging","marketing_angle":""},{"value":"Food heritage (nasi lemak, satay, rendang)","importance":"Low","expression":"Deep culinary pride; food unites Malaysians; safe for brand connections; be careful with \"origin\" claims","marketing_angle":""},{"value":"Rainforest and natural heritage","importance":"Low","expression":"Taman Negara (oldest rainforest); biodiversity pride; orangutans; environmental stewardship","marketing_angle":""}]',
    c.communication_norms = '{"context_type":"HIGH_CONTEXT","directness":"INDIRECT","hierarchy_sensitivity":"HIGH"}',
    c.culture_summary = 'en-MY: Communication style is indirect. Hierarchy importance: high. Orientation: Collectivist (focus on \'we/together\'). Core values: Muhibbah (Racial Harmony), Family and community, Respect (Hormat).',
    c.taboos_summary = 'CRITICAL TABOOS: Race relations and racial policies, Religious issues and comparisons, Royalty (Raja-raja Melayu). Always avoid these topics.',
